executor_display_name: Lat/Long SQL where clause for Radius
executor_description: Use this API to build the SQL WHERE clause to use in your own database to search by latitude/longitude in a radius. You specify the latitude and longitude of center point, the distance/radius from this location, the field names used in your database for latitude and longitude, and a precision. The higher the precision, the more detailed the SQL string will be and the more accurate the results will be. A precision of 2 gives decent results for short distances. Larger distances might require a higher precision. To make your database queries efficient, you should create an index on the latitude/longitude pair in your database.
